					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6290006#post-3861419</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6290006/scp-4160#post-3861419</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 04 Jul 2018 06:42:06 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>mojitheblue</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>2422724</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>Not Mr. Rogers you monster!</p> <p>But seriously good article, it's a nice little look into another world, I agree with djkaktus 100%, +1</p> <p>I did notice a sentence that might need a rewrite:</p> <p>'pursue November 15th to be declared' reads a little weird to me, I think changing it to 'pursue the day of November 15th to be declared' reads more naturally, and second I think there could be some clarification/separation of world governments vs individual nations, as well as addressing how the Foundation plans to explain away November 15th being a national holiday in practically every country.</p> <p>My suggestion would be list a few world powers by region, (EU, North America, Russia and it's satellite states), as the big fish targets, mention that the holidays in the major regions must be sufficiently different in their history to avoid arousing suspicion, and that smaller countries will for the most part take care of themselves as few people outside them probably know their state holidays, I think something along those lines would serve to flesh out the holiday campaign a bit.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
