					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6290006#post-3860965</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6290006/scp-4160#post-3860965</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 03 Jul 2018 21:09:12 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Jacob Conwell</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1372582</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>I was just thinking the other day that there weren't any Mister Rogers skips, and now here we are and I'm sorry I asked. :(</p> </blockquote> <p>Apologies to Mr. Fred Rogers.</p> <blockquote> <p>I thought the 'voices' part was incredibly silly, not to mention extremely helpful in explaining what was going on, which I never enjoy. It really threw me out of the article.</p> </blockquote> <p>And that is fair. During the drafting phrase, it became apparent that not a lot of people are familiar with the muses of Greco-Roman myth and the voices served as a means of making the article more approachable to more readers. Admittedly it threw subtlety away, and it is quite silly, but then again Greco-Roman mythology can be quite the silly place. Such is life.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
