ref="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/zyn" >Zyn</a></span> - <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3353">SCP-3353</a></li> <li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drbleep" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2887044&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1530604090" alt="DrBleep" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2887044)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drbleep" >DrBleep</a></span> - <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3703">SCP-3703</a></li> <li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1530604090" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" >PeppersGhost</a></span> - <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3760">SCP-3760</a></li> <li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weryllium" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=2727655&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1530604090" alt="Weryllium" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=2727655)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/weryllium" >Weryllium</a></span> - <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/scp-3435">SCP-3435</a></li> <li><span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=778357&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1530604090" alt="ProcyonLotor" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=778357)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/procyonlotor" >ProcyonLotor</a></span> - <a href="http://www.scpwiki.com/every-damn-time">Every Damn Time</a></li> </ul> </div> </div> </div> <p>For those interested in spoilers:</p> <div class="collapsible-block"> <div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;show&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none"> <div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">–&nbsp;hide&nbsp;block</a></div> <div class="collapsible-block-content"> <p>Year after year, the muse Clio has attempted to inspire a history lesson on 15/11, only to have the attempt blocked by her sister muse Melpomene. There is a certain tragedy in failing to fulfil your main purpose in your pantheon, afterall. This has continued through out history, in different eras. Melpomene only finally lost interest in tormenting her sister when Clio finally managed to have the inspired lecture completed with the help of the Foundation.</p> <p>This does beg the question, however, that if the muses of Greco-Roman myth are hanging around, what other members of the Pantheon also exist.</p> </div> </div> </div> <p>Thanks for the read.</p> <p><em>JC</em></p> 
